The paper deals with decision lists, which are a topic in both complexity theory and learning theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are both likely categories. The paper also involves analyzing how decision lists simplify under random restrictions, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may also be a relevant category. Additionally, decision lists are used in artificial intelligence and information theory, so cs.AI and cs.IT are also possible categories.
